G. Merchant Acquisition Business
G.1 Deployment of Third Party PoS Terminals
36.
A UCB not intending to act as Point of Sale (POS) acquiring bank is permitted
to deploy third party POS terminals without prior approval of RBI subject to
fulfilling the following criteria:
(1) A UCB is licensed by RBI and is Core Banking Solution (CBS) compliant;
(2) The CRAR is not less than nine percent in the preceding financial year;
(3) A UCB has recorded a net profit in the preceding financial year;
(4) The Board of a UCB consists of at least two professional directors;
(5) A UCB has a Board approved customer grievance redressal mechanism;
(6) A UCB has put in place a policy approved by the Board for merchant
acquisition for card transactions;
(7) There are no restrictions imposed on the UCB for accepting deposits /
withdrawals by the RBI;
(8) A UCB obtains consent from its merchant customers before offering third
party POS terminals and discloses the settlement process; and
(9) A UCB reports the operationalization of third-party POS terminals to the
respective Department of Supervision, RBI within a month, along with
the necessary documents.
